This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the generation of natural language using neural language models. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as neural language models are a subset of these fields. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with neural models. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it discusses the impact of neural language models on authorship attribution.
